The area

Neighborhood: Downtown Dubai
You canâ€™t fail to miss Dubaiâ€™s iconic Burj Khalifa, the worldâ€™s tallest building. It towers over the city and resides in the prestigious Downtown development. Once an old army base, Downtown is now the jewel in Dubaiâ€™s crown, a beautiful residential and leisure area housing not only the worldâ€™s tallest building, but the worldâ€™s largest fountains and mall. Wide marble sidewalks are perfect for strolling, with restaurants, art galleries and childrenâ€™s play areas. Specially commissioned sculptures line the roads and Downtown is often used as a canvas for modern art displays and community events such as Classic Car Shows and National Day parades. In the cooler months, cross one of the many bridges to the Burj Khalifa park and enjoy a picnic alongside residents and visitors, or enjoy a lunch or dinner watch the dancing fountains. Because of its mixed use, Downtown is a fantastic place to mix with Dubai residents and locals and watch real life unfold in a cosmopolitan environment.

    Didn't have time to do it justice
    If you use public transfer to get to it and get off at Burj Khalifa/Dubai Mall metro stop you should be aware that the station is about 10-15 walk away from the actual Mall itself but the walk way is under cover and air conditioned. We spent several hours there but my wife and daughters didn't think we had time to do it justice. There is a whole floor of eateries and the shops go from the expected "very high end very expensive" to H&M. It contains a massive aquarium which has a huge transparent wall you can look into and there is the free Fountain Show from about 6:30 in the evening so you might want to go in the afternoon. I suppose there is slight surreal/excess feel to the place but you should go and see it.

  • Deanosaur89
    Edmonton, Canada8,742 contributions
    Easily Spent too much time here
    We didn't want to spend too much time here but found ourselves here almost everyday during our trip to Dubai. There is a lot to see and some very nice shops and restaurants. The Dubai Mall is part of the great Downtown Dubai area and is connected to the Burj Khalifa and offers a variety of terraces to view the Dubai Fountains and Burj area. We did quite a bit of window shopping and buying here as there are a lot of brands from all over the world and we felt we got some good deals on some new clothes, shoes and other items too. When we went in November there was lots of Christmas items and displays that we appreciated. The best part about this mall is how clean and well maintained it is. There are a lot of different themed areas and the mall itself is nicely organized to have similar shops in the same area. For example there is an area called Fashion Avenue which has more of the upscale fashion brands, a Souq area with Arabic style shops, there is Chinatown which has restaurants and stores catered to Chinese, a sports area, children's clothes area, etc. There are many attractions in the mall too like an ice skating rink, a giant aquarium and indoor art installations. There are also quite a few domed areas and nicely decorated walls that look great in pictures. The At the Top experience for Burj Khalifa can also be accessed from inside the Dubai Mall. The mall is connected to the Dubai Metro at Burj Khalifa/Dubai Mall station via a long pedway system which takes about 15 minutes to get to. The mall is truly overwhelming and worth spending a few hours at to just look around if you enjoy malls. There is also a Dubai Mall application that can help navigate the mall to find specific stores or attractions. The application stopped working a few times for us but we found closing and opening it up again helped us. We found ourselves coming back again and again to either try a different experience or restaurant.
    Visited November 2023
    Traveled as a couple
